# macro_check

This Python package provides a utility function `perform_macro_check(filepath)` to detect the presence of macros in common document formats:

- `.doc`, `.xls`, `.ppt` (OLE-based)
- `.docx`, `.xlsx`, `.pptx` (OpenXML)
- `.pdf` (for embedded JavaScript/OpenAction)

## Usage

```python
from macro_check.checker import perform_macro_check

result = perform_macro_check("sample.docm")
print(result)


